        (115331, 'John Indrisano', '1905-11-01', 'Born in East Boston, Johnny Indrisano was from a poverty stricken  family. As a youth he vowed to "have money" some day. He boxed 155  amateur fights. He turned professional and went on to fight 83 main  events in which he won 80. He defeated 5 world champions. His career  lasted from 1924 to 1934. He defeated among others, Joe Dundee(World  Welterweight Champ/non-title fight), Nick Testo, Johnny Freeman, Sig  Keppen, and Sammy Baker. From 1934 to 1949 he worked as a boxing  referee. He began as a boxing coach for movie stars and from there  became a full-time boxing adviser on films. He also worked as a  character actor. Among the stars he trained were John Garfield, Spencer  Tracy, Carey Grant, Mickey Rooney, Robert Ryan, Robert Taylor, Jimmy  Durante, Fred MacMurray, Ricardo Montalban, and William Lundigan. He  died under mysterious conditions - possibly a suicide.

