        (133612, 'Ase Wang', '1981-11-26', 'Ase, one of the most successful young models in Thailand, comes from a background of mixed heritage with Chinese and Swedish parentage. She is fluent in English, Swedish and semi-fluent in Mandarin and Thai. Having grown up in Singapore, but based in Bangkok, Thailand, she has worked in various countries across the globe and starred in over twenty commercials which have aired worldwide. Ase trained at The Lee Strasberg Theatre &amp; Film Institute in New York and her time is predominantly split between Hong Kong, China, Japan, Thailand and Los Angeles.

After landing a lead role in the Singaporean TV series SPIN (similar to 90210), her career began to take flight. Audiences really engaged with her character "Pepper" and shortly after, she was offered a starring role in her first Singaporean feature film, CLOUDS IN MY COFFEE, a small indie film about three women coming of age. After this successful brief stint in Singapore, Ase moved her career to Hong Kong, where she appeared in many commercials and music videos along side stars such as, Aaron Kwok and she was named one of FHM''s Sexiest Women of Asia for 4 years running. Ase recently wrapped a lead role in her first Hollywood feature, PRINCE AND ME 4: THE ELEPHANT ADVENTURE, playing the beautiful "Princess Myra," part of a tragic pair of star-crossed lovers.

Initially pursued as a hobby, Ases'' continued passion for horse riding has now seen her with over 15 years of trained experience, having competed in various competitions in show jumping and dressage. Aside from her acting and modeling career, Ase designed her own clothing line in collaboration with CPS CHAPS, under the sub-brand, CPS CHAPS By ASE WANG, with the items being sold exclusively in the several flagship stores across the country. Much of her time off-set was spent designing her clothing line with her team and acting as the spokesperson for the brand in various promotional activities.', 'Singapore', 1, '/A3CqrCvSApM3hYAK0vZ1JFWMcTi.jpg'),
